components.chosen_design:
Single Model struct holding all device tensors keyed by layer, with a per-layer dispatch on a precomputed is_recurrent[il] bool (il where (il+1)%4==0 are FULL attention: il=3,7,...; the other 24/48 are LINEAR/GDN). One forward(tokens, positions, &mut Cache) that loops 0..n_layer and branches full vs linear, runs final output_norm + lm_head. A separate forward_mtp(token, h_seed, &mut Cache) for the NextN head. Stage 1 = correctness-first: implement the GDN recurrence as the plain autoregressive scalar-gate scan (decode) + a simple sequential/chunk-free prefill scan (loop over tokens reusing the decode step) so prefill==decode by construction — match logits to llama.cpp before any chunked/fused fast path. Stage 2 = port the fused warp kernel for speed. Recurrence math is the SAME for prefill and decode (just iterate t); this is the safest correctness anchor.

DUAL CACHE (the 24GB / long-ctx win):
- GROWING KV cache ONLY for the 8 full-attn layers (9B: il 3,7,11,...,31; 27B: 16 layers; +1 for the MTP block). Per layer per token: K = n_embd_k_gqa = head_dim*n_head_kv = 256*4 = 1024 floats, V same = 1024. So KV bytes/token (9B, 8 layers, fp16) = 8*2*1024*2 = 32 KiB/token => 262144-ctx ~= 8 GiB. This is the only part that grows with context.
- FIXED recurrent state for the 24 linear layers, independent of context length: per layer per sequence: conv_state n_embd_r = (d_conv-1)*(d_inner+2*n_group*d_state) = 3*8192 = 24576 floats; ssm_state n_embd_s = d_state*d_inner = 128*4096 = 524288 floats. 9B: 24 layers * (24576 + 524288) * 4B = ~52.7 MiB per sequence, CONSTANT for any context length. (Mirrors llama_hparams::n_embd_r()/n_embd_s() lines 204/221.) This constant-size recurrent state for 75% of layers is exactly why the hybrid fits long context in 24GB. Allocate as two flat buffers per linear layer: conv_states[n_embd_r, n_seqs], ssm_states[S_v*S_v*H_v, n_seqs]=[524288,n_seqs]. Update in place each step (conv: shift-in newest col; ssm: overwrite with new S).

RUST MODULE LAYOUT:
- model.rs: Model { hparams, embd, output_norm, output, layers: Vec<Layer>, mtp: Option<MtpBlock> }
- layer.rs: enum LayerKind { FullAttn(FullAttnW), Linear(LinearW) } + shared { attn_norm, post_attn_norm, ffn(gate/up/down or moe) }
- cache.rs: Cache { kv: Vec<KvLayer> (only full-attn idxs), recur: Vec<RecurLayer> (conv_state, ssm_state) }
- forward.rs: forward(), forward_full_attn(), forward_linear_attn() (-> build_conv + gdn_scan + gated_norm), forward_ffn(), forward_mtp()
- gdn.rs: gdn_scan kernel wrapper (decode + prefill).
